    "Management": {
      "text": "If you suspect Beriberi then treat it! Diagnosis is clinical and difficult to confirm, treatment is simple/inexpensive/effective, there is little risk to treatment, and the risk of morbidity/mortality from not treating is high\nThiamine\n50-100mg IV/IM q day x 7-14 days, then 10mg PO q day until complete recovery\nMagnesium\n; hypomagnesemic state may be resistant to thiamine administration\nMultivitamin (at risk for other vitamin deficiencies)\nGive thiamine BEFORE glucose in patients requiring glucose who are at risk for thiamine deficiency; glucose without thiamine can precipitate/worsen WE by driving thiamine intracellularly",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
